Project: Semantic Search Engine for Customer Complaints using PySpark + Sentence-Transformers
ğŸ¯ Goal

Build a semantic search system where users can search for customer complaints or problem descriptions (e.g., â€œwashing machine not drainingâ€), and the system retrieves similar complaints from a large dataset â€” even if the exact words differ.

For example:

Query: â€œwater not coming into washing machineâ€

Matched results: â€œno water flow detectedâ€, â€œmachine not fillingâ€, â€œinlet valve issueâ€

ğŸ§© 1. Use Case
Background

In a large appliance company, millions of customer complaints are stored in a database.
Traditional keyword search (SQL LIKE queries) fails because:

Users describe the same issue using different words.

Spelling and phrasing vary widely.

We need semantic search â€” where meaning matters more than exact words.

